&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Homerton University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant Physician in Dermatology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Permanent post - Full time/Part time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Homerton is an innovative Foundation Trust providing a wide range of services to its local community and specialist services on a regional level. Located in East End of London we are close to the heart of the capital and our local population is young and culturally diverse. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Trust wishes to appoint a Consultant Dermatologist, to join our expanding Consultant team which is currently made up of Dr Richard Bull, Dr Portia Goldsmith, Dr Louise Fuller, Dr Abha Gulati, Dr Andrew Lock, Dr Anna Chapman and Dr Mary Sommerlad.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With a job plan comprising of weekly adult, paediatric and skin cancer clinics. This is an excellent general dermatology opportunity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is therefore an exciting opportunity for an ambitious, dynamic and enthusiastic clinician to grow the Trust’s Dermatology service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: Friday 11th December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Informal enquiries are welcome, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Abha Gulati on 020 8510 7690.&lt;/p&gt;
